HEADWORD: Antimacassar
<hw>An`ti*ma*cas"sar</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n`t⟦icr⟧*m⟦adot⟧*k⟦acr⟧s"s⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
cover for the back or arms of a chair or sofa, etc., to prevent them
from wear or from being soiled by macassar or other oil from the
hair.</def>⟦br⟧
